09/06/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Police have arrested an ethnic Serb wanted by Croatia for war crimes committed in 1991, media reported on Tuesday (June 8th). Marin Krivosic, 45, was detained on Saturday based on an arrest warrant issued by Zagreb. He is suspected of involvement in the killing of 56 Croatian civilians in the village of Bacin early in the 1991-1995 Croatian war. A former Serb paramilitary member, Krivosic will remain in custody pending extradition procedures. (RTCG, Tanjug, AP, AFP - 08/06/10)
